'''Homelessness Australia''' (HA) is the national [[peak body organisation]] for homelessness services and homeless people in Australia. The organisation provides systemic advocacy for the sector and works in collaboration with support services, state and national homelessness organisations, other peak organisations, government agencies and the broader community. Homelessness Australia was formed in late 1998 as the '''Australian Federation of Homelessness Organisations''' (AFHO) by the Council to Homeless Persons Australia (CHPA), National Youth Coalition for Housing (NYCH), and Women's Services Network (WESNET). The organisation was established with the mission of advancing research and promoting national policy and action to reduce homelessness.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.homelessnessaustralia.org.au/index.php/about-us/what-we-do|title=What We Do|publisher=Homelessness Australia}}</ref>
==Positions== The organisation maintains that without strong national peak bodies, government decision makers may ignore the important welfare issues of affordable housing and homelessness.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.shelter.org.au/housing-supply-media-releases/joint-statement-national-shelter-community-housing-federation|title=Joint statement from National Shelter, Community Housing Federation of Australia and Homelessness Australia - Shelter (National)|publisher=}}</ref>
HA and other homelessness services launched a #VoteHome campaign, proposing that government assist in halving the number of homeless by 2025.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.smh.com.au/nsw/mission-australia-anglicare-unitingcare-the-salvation-army-wesley-mission-and-st-vincent-de-paul-pressure-government-on-homelessness-20160523-gp1am9.html|title='I ended up losing everything': How a shoulder injury set Ian's life off course|first=Rachel|last=Browne|date=24 May 2016|publisher=Sydney Morning Herald}}</ref>
HA has stated that the often cited statistics on homelessness do not reflect those "on the verge" of homelessness, which they estimate to be at 850,000.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://theconversation.com/ghost-hunting-will-the-census-reveal-the-true-scale-of-homelessness-in-australia-63336|title=Ghost-hunting: will the census reveal the true scale of homelessness in Australia?|first=Eileen|last=Webb|publisher=}}</ref>
==Events== Since 2007, Homelessness Australia has coordinated a national awareness week for homeless people, [[Homeless Persons' Week]].
